### Conflicts
No conflicts as of last run.

QSignalMapper has actually been un-deprecated, see [QSignalMapper deprecation](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-73407) and [Un-deprecate QSignalMapper](https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtbase/+/268701).

However Concept ACK assuming there's no change in behaviour and the new code is still compatible with Qt `5.5.1`.

@fanquake 
> QSignalMapper has actually been un-deprecated, see [QSignalMapper deprecation](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-73407) and [Un-deprecate QSignalMapper](https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtbase/+/268701).

I didn't know about that. Thank you.

From [Un-deprecate QSignalMapper](https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtbase/+/268701):
> ... Note that in most cases y
Concept ACK -- more readable and less code

Post merge ACK. This totally gets rid of the flood of warnings on macOs with QT 5.13 from homebrew.  It's also shorter and more readable. Tested that external explorer links still work, as well as banning peers.\n\nBuilding with depends (QT 5.9.7) also works, though this still throws trillions of (unrelated) warnings.
